{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nEpic 88ab (elfish-chair-lug) S3. R3 requires BOTH votes on every feature-branch change and on the merge change. The design EXPECTED g2p dispatch to be branch-agnostic; this story VERIFIES that and, per the verified finding below, REMEDIATES the gap it exposes. ASSUMES epic 1fa8 (smoky-flare-slug) is complete (g2p installed, gerrit-verify.yaml exists, two-vote submit active).\n\n## VERIFIED FINDING (drives the revised scope)\ng2p does NOT branch-filter dispatch (source: lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform@44d5d46 patchset_created.py / github.py / helpers.py — event->workflow mapping is filename-substring based, no branch keys in gerrit_to_platform.ini). BUT g2p dispatches via GitHub `workflow_dispatch(ref=refs/heads/{GERRIT_BRANCH})`, which REQUIRES that ref to EXIST on the GitHub mirror to resolve the workflow file. `replication.config` replicates only refs/heads/main + refs/tags/* + refs/changes/* — NOT refs/heads/feature/*. So a feature/* change's dispatch targets a non-existent GitHub ref -> 422/no-op -> the change gets LLM-Review but NEVER Verified and can never satisfy the two-vote gate. Proven live: change 198 on feature/s3-ci got LLM-Review+1 and zero CI. This is the exact failure the story exists to catch.\n\n## What (REVISED — includes the remediation)\n- **AC1 (verified statement):** record the g2p branch-filtering finding above (config or no-op) with source citation in the ini spec / a short g2p-dispatch note.\n- **FIX (new, required for the story's CI-coverage evidence):** `infra/gerrit/replication.config` — add `push = refs/heads/feature/*:refs/heads/feature/*` to `[remote \"github\"]`, scoped to feature/* (NOT a wildcard, never refs/meta/*), so the workflow_dispatch ref resolves. Documented tradeoff: feature branches become transiently visible on the mirror (deleted after merge-back; teardown handled by S6 inventory + merge-back cleanup). **Deploy** to the running Gerrit via the gerrit_etc volume; `autoReload = true` in replication.config means the plugin re-reads on change with NO Gerrit restart (verified). Back-out: remove the line; a `.bak-s3` of the prior config is kept on the box.\n- Verify `checkout-gerrit-change-action` fetches a MERGE refspec so CI builds the actual merge tree (get_change_refspec computes refs/changes/NN/NNNN/P identically for merge + normal commits — the patchset ref IS the merge tree; run-log evidence).\n- Prove with run-log evidence: (a) a feature/* patchset-created triggers gerrit-verify.yaml and casts Verified (POST-FIX); (b) a merge change into main gets CI on the merge tree; (c) Verified RE-RUNS (does not carry) on a re-merge (MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE); (d) `concurrency: cancel-in-progress` behaves sanely across concurrent branch + merge changes.\n\n## Scope\ng2p config + workflow verification + evidence, PLUS the replication.config feature/* fix + its live deployment (the prerequisite that makes feature/* CI possible — without it none of the run-log ACs can be produced). No label/ACL config (S1), no bot code (S2), no doc prose beyond the ini/dispatch spec (S4). The replication change is the minimal remediation, not new gate behavior.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Verified statement on g2p branch filtering recorded (config or no-op), with source/doc citation, in the ini/dispatch spec\n- [ ] replication.config replicates feature/* (committed) AND deployed live via autoReload (no restart); a newly-created feature branch auto-replicates to the GitHub mirror (proven)\n- [ ] Run-log evidence: feature/* patchset triggers gerrit-verify.yaml and casts Verified (post-fix)\n- [ ] Run-log evidence: merge change gets CI on the actual merge tree via the merge refspec\n- [ ] Run-log evidence: Verified re-runs on a re-merge; no carry observed\n- [ ] Concurrency behavior across branch + merge changes documented with a run example"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783062191629230001,"uuid":"389fd8cd-7695-44d3-91fd-f5447ddda450"}